column4: This free one-day festival partnered with Amp the Cause, a group that helps support more than 50 child-focused health and education organizations, and other sponsors to create a downtown Denver music festival that caters to all ages. The event has a five-stage lineup, more than 25 bands, food trucks, and lots of family-friendly entertainment. This is a festival you and the family won't want to miss!

The Greenway Trail, a paved bike trail, follows the South Platte River for almost 30 miles, connecting a necklace of riverside parks. Since much of Denver's early history occurred along this river, the Colorado Historical Society has erected more than 20 large historic signs that use photos and illustrations to tell the story of the area.
